Independence rage.

00:18.600 --> 00:21.960
<i>Scotland's share of the oil revenues</i>
<i>has been far too high for too long.</i>

00:22.040 --> 00:23.200
Stop it!

00:23.280 --> 00:24.880
-That's not me.
-Certainly looks like you.

00:24.960 --> 00:26.480
It's a fake. That's a fake.

00:29.000 --> 00:30.600
Redback has got
to be bigger than this.

00:30.680 --> 00:34.440
They came within a ball hair
of killing the Prime Minister.

00:34.520 --> 00:35.760
Drop the gun!

00:36.360 --> 00:39.280
We believe the attempt on your life
was funded by a group

00:39.360 --> 00:41.760
who are also
backing Scottish terrorists.

00:41.840 --> 00:43.400
I've been brought
into the inner sanctum.

00:43.480 --> 00:45.640
Pub on the Borders
in two or three days.

00:45.720 --> 00:47.160
Localised explosion.

00:47.240 --> 00:48.560
Maximum publicity.

00:48.640 --> 00:49.640
Tell Laird it's on.

00:49.720 --> 00:51.720
This could cost us the union.

01:40.720 --> 01:43.800
And it's scheduled already, is it,
for tomorrow afternoon, this action?

01:44.600 --> 01:45.880
Once you approve it, yes.

01:46.520 --> 01:49.120
You see, the difficulty
is that it's not in my hands

01:49.200 --> 01:51.760
because the pub is Danish-owned.

01:52.320 --> 01:55.000
So, I've had to run this
past Michael Jespersen,

01:56.000 --> 01:57.840
who has delegated the decision

01:59.440 --> 02:00.400
to his deputy.

02:02.800 --> 02:03.640
Poulsen?

02:06.840 --> 02:08.200
Oh, God.

02:10.320 --> 02:12.640
I've been on this for two years.

02:13.960 --> 02:16.640
What, now I've got to bring
in someone who I don't even trust?

03:22.840 --> 03:23.760
Temple Laird.

03:24.520 --> 03:26.080
Scottish nationalist terrorist.

03:26.720 --> 03:29.080
Intel has him behind three attacks
on English-owned properties

03:29.160 --> 03:31.280
and two on European businesses
this year.

03:31.760 --> 03:33.360
He's been arrested four times.

03:33.440 --> 03:35.920
Police can never find
the evidence to charge him.

03:36.000 --> 03:37.280
And no fatalities?

03:37.880 --> 03:39.240
No. So far he's always called it in,

03:39.320 --> 03:41.400
but narratives like his
always end in murder.

03:41.480 --> 03:44.120
I thought you were gonna concentrate
on Redback.

03:44.720 --> 03:47.400
We believe that Laird
is funded by Russian money.

03:47.480 --> 03:49.480
-You believe?
-Can we just concentrate on Laird?

03:49.560 --> 03:52.640
You think that Russia
would fund a terror attack in the UK?

03:52.720 --> 03:54.800
I've seen a Russian terror attack
in the middle of London.

03:54.880 --> 03:58.520
I watched the agonising deaths
of two men, so...

04:00.480 --> 04:04.680
Listen, what you're talking about,
those were isolated attacks.

04:05.280 --> 04:06.560
What we're trying to assess

04:06.640 --> 04:10.600
is whether this lunatic is capable
of a mass-fatality event.

04:10.680 --> 04:12.120
Sorry. Do you think
we're winging this?

04:12.200 --> 04:14.400
We've been tracking him
for two years.

04:15.040 --> 04:17.960
All of our reports are verified
by forensic psychologists.

04:18.040 --> 04:19.080
He is dangerous.

04:19.680 --> 04:21.680
And in 24 hours we can lock him up.

04:22.360 --> 04:23.600
OK, Laird's cell.

04:24.280 --> 04:26.000
Do you have an agent
embedded with them?

04:26.400 --> 04:27.400
Yes.

04:27.480 --> 04:28.960
Well, then I need to speak to them.

04:32.160 --> 04:33.840
<i>Look, as soon as we've won</i>
<i>the referendum,</i>

04:33.920 --> 04:36.920
<i>I will of course renegotiate</i>
<i>the Continental Shelf Act.</i>

04:37.520 --> 04:40.040
<i>I mean, it's obvious.</i>
<i>Scotland's share of the oil revenues</i>

04:40.120 --> 04:42.200
<i>has been far too high</i>
<i>for far too long.</i>

04:43.040 --> 04:44.600
How are they getting away with it?

04:44.680 --> 04:46.200
How do people not realise?

04:46.280 --> 04:48.440
I think they do.
I think people know it's a fake.

04:48.960 --> 04:51.120
Really?
That's not what we're getting.

04:51.200 --> 04:52.040
Tell me.

04:54.200 --> 04:56.760
Private polling... Forget...
Forget what the papers are saying.

04:57.720 --> 05:01.560
Private polling has support for
Scottish independence at 53 percent.

05:04.960 --> 05:07.600
Do you still think most people
believe the film's a fake?

05:09.440 --> 05:11.800
The revolt against reason continues.

05:13.280 --> 05:15.920
Idiocrasy in your own party
fans the flames.

05:16.000 --> 05:19.200
People choose to believe the film
because of your honesty,

05:19.960 --> 05:22.040
which is a drum
you're very fond of beating.

05:22.680 --> 05:24.560
Makes them feel bad about themselves.

05:26.400 --> 05:28.960
The film gives them an opportunity
to tell you to fuck off.

05:34.320 --> 05:35.880
I should kill the referendum.

05:37.720 --> 05:38.520
Resign.

05:39.400 --> 05:40.200
No.

05:40.280 --> 05:42.160
Mr. Ogilvy
thinks it's the best option.

05:42.240 --> 05:43.640
I think it's the only option.

05:43.720 --> 05:45.800
Absolutely not. Adam...

05:47.720 --> 05:48.920
We're gonna win this.

06:01.800 --> 06:03.000
I didn't agree to this!

06:03.080 --> 06:03.880
Hey.

06:04.640 --> 06:06.440
Katrine Poulsen. DSIS.

06:08.640 --> 06:12.040
And I didn't agree to you planting
a bomb in a pub, but here we are.

06:12.120 --> 06:16.040
Because the pub is Danish-owned
we had to run it past DSIS.

06:18.760 --> 06:19.560
So?

06:21.400 --> 06:23.600
Why doesn't Laird
plant the bomb himself?

06:28.160 --> 06:29.840
Laird's a strategist, all right?

06:30.680 --> 06:33.360
He never handles explosives.
His dad's old SNLA mate,

06:33.440 --> 06:35.720
Deke McAllister,
assembles the devices.

06:36.320 --> 06:39.160
Laird's father blew himself up
when Laird was ten.

06:39.240 --> 06:40.480
When the device is operational,

06:40.560 --> 06:42.680
Laird gets one of his soldiers
to do the rest.

06:43.280 --> 06:45.280
OK. Talk me through it.

06:48.400 --> 06:50.320
Right, so tomorrow
I pick up the package.

06:51.920 --> 06:53.280
<i>I drive out to The Skanda pub.</i>

06:53.360 --> 06:55.960
<i>I head into the gents</i>
<i>where I disable the bomb.</i>

06:56.720 --> 06:59.760
<i>Slide it into a cupboard space</i>
<i>and then call in the warning.</i>

07:00.760 --> 07:03.080
But the bomb
has never been touched by Laird.

07:03.160 --> 07:04.520
Kelvin will have car trouble.

07:04.600 --> 07:06.920
He'll call Laird.
Laird will pick him up.

07:07.000 --> 07:08.920
The police will follow Laird.
I'm wearing a wire.

07:09.000 --> 07:11.600
No, no, no. No wire.
No, we went through this.

07:11.680 --> 07:13.880
-It's a risk we can't take.
-OK, OK. No wire.

07:15.920 --> 07:18.640
As soon as Laird drops me off,
the police pull him over.

07:18.720 --> 07:21.680
And then the TNT residue from Kelvin
links Laird to the bomb.

07:22.840 --> 07:24.280
GPS for Laird's croft.

07:26.080 --> 07:27.200
And just in case...

07:29.760 --> 07:31.120
The transmitter's in Laird's lighter.

07:31.200 --> 07:32.600
I didn't tell you to do that.

07:33.040 --> 07:34.120
Nobody saw me.

07:35.840 --> 07:38.080
How dangerous is Temple Laird?

07:38.440 --> 07:39.640
Jesus Christ.

07:40.600 --> 07:42.200
He's insane! All right?

07:42.280 --> 07:45.280
He's sourced AK-47s
and suicide vests.

07:45.360 --> 07:46.880
And if independence doesn't happen,

07:46.960 --> 07:48.880
he will carry out
a mass-casualty attack.

07:48.960 --> 07:50.560
Have you seen anything like that?

07:50.640 --> 07:53.480
You're planting a live bomb
in a crowded pub!

07:53.560 --> 07:54.840
It won't be live.

07:54.920 --> 07:58.360
Look, I was yodi for three years
in Afghanistan

07:58.440 --> 08:00.520
and I dealt with 100 roadside bombs.

08:00.600 --> 08:01.800
I know what I'm
doing!

08:03.200 --> 08:04.760
Is this happening or not?

08:09.200 --> 08:10.200
I don't know.

08:13.520 --> 08:15.560
Just leave it with me,
all right? Just...

08:34.000 --> 08:35.240
What's that on your phone?

08:36.760 --> 08:37.600
Oh.

08:38.320 --> 08:39.320
When I was asleep,

08:40.040 --> 08:42.680
Theo wanted to tell me
that he loved me, so my wife said,

08:42.760 --> 08:44.440
"Let's leave a message
on Daddy's phone."

08:45.080 --> 08:47.440
Aw, that's the sweetest.

08:47.520 --> 08:48.880
He left you a message.

08:49.720 --> 08:50.800
What age is he?

08:50.880 --> 08:51.680
Twenty-seven.

08:53.280 --> 08:54.880
No, he'll be six next month.

08:54.960 --> 08:56.160
I love you.

08:59.840 --> 09:01.840
You know, if we lose Scotland,

09:01.920 --> 09:03.960
they become
the seventh richest nation.

09:04.560 --> 09:05.600
We drop to sixteenth.

09:05.680 --> 09:06.600
Seventeenth.

09:09.280 --> 09:10.400
God.

09:11.120 --> 09:13.120
Adam's taking a massive risk.

09:15.400 --> 09:16.480
There is a solution.

09:18.360 --> 09:19.960
But I can't suggest it to Adam.

09:24.040 --> 09:25.000
What is it?

09:25.680 --> 09:26.840
This solution?

09:30.640 --> 09:33.040
The referendum's
going to be a digital vote.

09:34.720 --> 09:38.960
I know people, who if needs be,
can tweak the results.

09:39.040 --> 09:41.920
Look, I know.
I can't believe I'm saying it, but

09:43.360 --> 09:46.720
if we lose, the economic impact...

09:46.800 --> 09:48.040
Like, people will die.

09:50.600 --> 09:52.600
If I made that suggestion...

09:52.680 --> 09:53.640
He'd fire you.

09:55.200 --> 09:56.480
I'd lose my oldest friend.

09:59.960 --> 10:01.080
What if it came from me?

10:29.640 --> 10:30.600
What's happened?

10:32.640 --> 10:33.960
Fucking spy.

10:35.800 --> 10:37.200
Infiltrator.

10:38.600 --> 10:39.560
Betrayal.

10:41.200 --> 10:44.040
Nothing worse. Nothing fucking worse.

10:47.880 --> 10:48.760
Who is it?

10:53.520 --> 10:54.480
Come here.

11:24.240 --> 11:25.120
Deke?

11:26.360 --> 11:27.840
I knew somebody was at it.

11:29.000 --> 11:29.840
Took me a while.

11:30.720 --> 11:31.520
I got proof.

11:37.600 --> 11:38.720
Both knees.

11:39.400 --> 11:41.600
No, don't do it. No!

11:43.480 --> 11:44.520
Do it.

11:47.200 --> 11:48.280
No, no.

11:49.480 --> 11:50.280
No!

11:51.440 --> 11:52.240
No!

11:53.920 --> 11:54.880
No!

11:57.360 --> 11:58.520
Do it!

12:07.000 --> 12:08.800
No, no, no.

12:13.720 --> 12:15.560
No...

12:25.040 --> 12:26.400
You were gonna shoot me.

12:29.200 --> 12:33.240
This little psycho
was gonna fucking kneecap me.

12:33.800 --> 12:37.480
Who's my little fucking psycho now,
you wee beauty?

12:39.000 --> 12:39.960
You passed the test, son.

12:40.840 --> 12:42.320
You're on for tomorrow.

12:43.080 --> 12:44.080
Right, give me that.

12:44.480 --> 12:45.760
Right, yous pricks.

12:46.520 --> 12:47.960
Let's have a fucking drink!

12:48.040 --> 12:48.880
Aye!

12:49.840 --> 12:50.920
He's shite-ing himself.

12:53.720 --> 12:55.360
I would have done it for the cause.

13:01.240 --> 13:02.040
Hey.

13:02.560 --> 13:05.400
So, my office sent information
on your guy.

13:06.720 --> 13:08.080
Kelvin Cruickshanks.

13:08.160 --> 13:11.280
Orphaned at four.
Seven failed attempts at fostering.

13:12.080 --> 13:15.040
On the plus side, he has a pretty
impressive list of petty crimes.

13:15.480 --> 13:17.720
Right, as a kid,
he took the blame for others.

13:18.880 --> 13:20.840
He's passed every security clearance.

13:20.920 --> 13:23.080
-He's 29 years old.
-Uh-uh.

13:23.160 --> 13:24.200
No relationships.

13:25.040 --> 13:26.720
His motives are adolescent.

13:26.800 --> 13:27.760
I don't agree.

13:27.840 --> 13:29.560
I want to make my mark.

13:30.480 --> 13:34.160
I mean, come on. Loneliness
and the need to be recognised.

13:34.240 --> 13:36.040
Well, he's vulnerable
to manipulation.

13:36.120 --> 13:37.640
He's a grown man.

13:37.720 --> 13:40.600
A grown man
that would do anything for you.

13:41.840 --> 13:43.480
I think it gives you a kick.

13:44.760 --> 13:47.240
So, do you ever think
before you speak?

13:47.320 --> 13:48.840
But the agent handler thing.

13:48.920 --> 13:51.360
That's more intense
than any love affair.

13:51.440 --> 13:53.960
When a lover
says, "I'll die for you,"

13:54.040 --> 13:55.040
they never mean it.

13:56.000 --> 13:57.520
But in our world, it's real.

13:59.360 --> 14:01.680
Are you gonna OK
this operation or not?

14:03.360 --> 14:05.120
No, I'm not going to OK it.

14:06.320 --> 14:07.800
I don't trust your agent.

14:10.080 --> 14:11.440
I don't trust you.

14:12.360 --> 14:14.000
But sometimes
you have to take a chance.

14:14.080 --> 14:15.480
Not with people's lives.

14:33.160 --> 14:34.000
Yes?

14:38.880 --> 14:41.520
Latest MORI,
Gallup and Harris Interactive.

14:41.600 --> 14:43.840
-Is there a consensus?
-We all think you're safe.

14:44.320 --> 14:46.720
Yea, well, they only register
the opinion of the polite.

14:52.280 --> 14:54.600
Zac says if we lose Scotland,
people will die.

14:55.480 --> 14:57.840
Yeah, well, Zac will probably
tell you exactly how many.

14:58.400 --> 14:59.600
It's avoidable.

14:59.680 --> 15:01.440
It is, if we win.

15:03.680 --> 15:04.880
We don't have to lose.

15:13.920 --> 15:14.800
